                            <p><strong>Fat</strong>: Not all fat is the same. In fact, healthy fats such as omega-3s are vital to your children&rsquo;s physical and emotional health. Including more healthy fat in your child&rsquo;s diet can help improve your child&rsquo;s mood, boost their well-being, and help them to be fit.</p>
                            <p><strong>Calcium</strong>: As well as leading to osteoporosis, not getting enough calcium in your child&rsquo;s diet can also contribute to anxiety, depression, and sleep difficulties. It&rsquo;s vital to include calcium-rich foods in your child&rsquo;s diet, limit those that deplete calcium, and get enough magnesium and vitamins D and K to help calcium do its job</p>
